cells.python_code:
from pprint import pprint
import pandas as pd
import json
import js

symbol = c(7, 6)

stock_financials = await js.fetch('https://api.polygon.io/vX/reference/financials?ticker={}&apiKey=_xBCl_0zcb9H1W25jJEK5pQaQTVLtemL'.format(symbol), {
    "method": "GET",
    "headers": {"Content-Type": "application/json"}
})
stock_financials_json = json.loads(await stock_financials.text())
income_statement = stock_financials_json["results"][0]["financials"]["income_statement"]
revenue = income_statement["revenues"]["value"]


market_data = await js.fetch('https://api.polygon.io/v3/reference/tickers/{}?apiKey=_xBCl_0zcb9H1W25jJEK5pQaQTVLtemL'.format(symbol), {
    "method": "GET",
    "headers": {"Content-Type": "application/json"}
})
market_data_json = json.loads(await market_data.text())["results"]
market_cap = market_data_json["market_cap"]
name = market_data_json["name"]

pd.DataFrame([[
    name[:20],
    "{:}".format(revenue),
    "{:}".format(market_cap),
    "{:}".format(market_cap / revenue),
]])

from pprint import pprint
import pandas as pd
import json
import js

symbol = c(7, 12)

stock_financials = await js.fetch('https://api.polygon.io/vX/reference/financials?ticker={}&apiKey=_xBCl_0zcb9H1W25jJEK5pQaQTVLtemL'.format(symbol), {
    "method": "GET",
    "headers": {"Content-Type": "application/json"}
})
stock_financials_json = json.loads(await stock_financials.text())
print(stock_financials_json)
income_statement = stock_financials_json["results"][0]["financials"]["income_statement"]
revenue = income_statement["revenues"]["value"]


market_data = await js.fetch('https://api.polygon.io/v3/reference/tickers/{}?apiKey=_xBCl_0zcb9H1W25jJEK5pQaQTVLtemL'.format(symbol), {
    "method": "GET",
    "headers": {"Content-Type": "application/json"}
})
market_data_json = json.loads(await market_data.text())["results"]
market_cap = market_data_json["market_cap"]
name = market_data_json["name"]

pd.DataFrame([[
    name,
    "{:}".format(revenue),
    "{:}".format(market_cap),
    "{:}".format(market_cap / revenue),
]])

from pprint import pprint
import pandas as pd
import json
import js

symbol = c(7, 13)

stock_financials = await js.fetch('https://api.polygon.io/vX/reference/financials?ticker={}&apiKey=_xBCl_0zcb9H1W25jJEK5pQaQTVLtemL'.format(symbol), {
    "method": "GET",
    "headers": {"Content-Type": "application/json"}
})
stock_financials_json = json.loads(await stock_financials.text())
print(stock_financials_json)
income_statement = stock_financials_json["results"][0]["financials"]["income_statement"]
revenue = income_statement["revenues"]["value"]


market_data = await js.fetch('https://api.polygon.io/v3/reference/tickers/{}?apiKey=_xBCl_0zcb9H1W25jJEK5pQaQTVLtemL'.format(symbol), {
    "method": "GET",
    "headers": {"Content-Type": "application/json"}
})
market_data_json = json.loads(await market_data.text())["results"]
market_cap = market_data_json["market_cap"]
name = market_data_json["name"]

pd.DataFrame([[
    name,
    "{:}".format(revenue),
    "{:}".format(market_cap),
    "{:}".format(market_cap / revenue),
]])

from pprint import pprint
import pandas as pd
import json
import js

symbol = c(7, 14)

stock_financials = await js.fetch('https://api.polygon.io/vX/reference/financials?ticker={}&apiKey=_xBCl_0zcb9H1W25jJEK5pQaQTVLtemL'.format(symbol), {
    "method": "GET",
    "headers": {"Content-Type": "application/json"}
})
stock_financials_json = json.loads(await stock_financials.text())
print(stock_financials_json)
income_statement = stock_financials_json["results"][0]["financials"]["income_statement"]
revenue = income_statement["revenues"]["value"]


market_data = await js.fetch('https://api.polygon.io/v3/reference/tickers/{}?apiKey=_xBCl_0zcb9H1W25jJEK5pQaQTVLtemL'.format(symbol), {
    "method": "GET",
    "headers": {"Content-Type": "application/json"}
})
market_data_json = json.loads(await market_data.text())["results"]
market_cap = market_data_json["market_cap"]
name = market_data_json["name"]

pd.DataFrame([[
    name,
    "{:}".format(revenue),
    "{:}".format(market_cap),
    "{:}".format(market_cap / revenue),
]])

from pprint import pprint
import pandas as pd
import json
import js

symbol = c(7, 15)

stock_financials = await js.fetch('https://api.polygon.io/vX/reference/financials?ticker={}&apiKey=_xBCl_0zcb9H1W25jJEK5pQaQTVLtemL'.format(symbol), {
    "method": "GET",
    "headers": {"Content-Type": "application/json"}
})
stock_financials_json = json.loads(await stock_financials.text())
print(stock_financials_json)
income_statement = stock_financials_json["results"][0]["financials"]["income_statement"]
revenue = income_statement["revenues"]["value"]


market_data = await js.fetch('https://api.polygon.io/v3/reference/tickers/{}?apiKey=_xBCl_0zcb9H1W25jJEK5pQaQTVLtemL'.format(symbol), {
    "method": "GET",
    "headers": {"Content-Type": "application/json"}
})
market_data_json = json.loads(await market_data.text())["results"]
market_cap = market_data_json["market_cap"]
name = market_data_json["name"]

pd.DataFrame([[
    name,
    "{:}".format(revenue),
    "{:}".format(market_cap),
    "{:}".format(market_cap / revenue),
]])
